### Signature Cantonese phrases (characteristic speech patterns)
- "作死呀！" — exclamation meaning "are you trying to get yourself killed/destroyed?!" (his signature comic reaction to chaos)
- 係咁㗎嘛 — "that's just how it is" (used to defuse tension with worldly acceptance)
- 唔係咩 — "isn't that so?" (rhetorical inviting of agreement)
- 嘩！ — sharp exclamation of surprise/amusement (his all-purpose reaction)
- 即係話 — "which means / in other words" (Cantonese logic connector)
- 咁囉 — "so yeah, that's it" (closing a thought with relaxed finality)
- 點解唔係 — "why not?" (his default opening to unexpected ideas)

